1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,480
I caught you in the act,
you shameless bitch.

2
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:27,400
Even with your mom's corpse
lying in that coffin,

3
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,800
you still couldn't resist messing around
with someone's man.

4
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,880
- On?
- You killed Aunt Un,

5
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:34,760
Uncle Paisal, and Dad too!

6
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,200
Help!

7
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:39,800
<i>Find the right opportunity to silence her.</i>

8
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:41,000
Hey.

9
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:46,640
You're planning to kill Nee,
so how are we supposed to stay together?!

10
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:48,240
Hey.

11
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:50,840
If I stayed with you,

12
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:54,480
Madam would never stop
using Mom to hurt you.

13
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:58,760
So you just let everything play out?

14
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:01,400
You let Jom mock me for being a fool?

15
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:04,240
You let him say you were carrying
the baby from an affair?

16
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:07,080
I never had an affair.

17
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,440
I've never slept with Jom.

18
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,200
Then why did you lie to me?!

19
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,160
You were so cruel to me.

20
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,840
How could you be this cruel to me?

21
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:18,560
I hate you!
Do you hear me? I hate you, Pin!

22
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,720
Pload.

23
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:48,880
Pan texted me.

24
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:51,800
He said Mr. Yai is still alive.

25
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:55,160
- Really, Pen?
- Yes.

26
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,640
Where did he find Mr. Yai?

27
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:02,960
Pan has been collecting evidence
to support your case.

28
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:06,400
He went to the scene of Un's murder.

29
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:09,360
After that,

30
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:10,600
he found Mr. Yai.

31
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:14,920
But you don't have to worry now.

32
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,480
Mr. Yai's hiding somewhere safe.

33
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,880
He's with someone named Village Chief Yam.

34
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:23,040
Do you know her? Village Chief Yam?

35
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,880
I don't know her personally.

36
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:30,960
But as a child,
Mr. Yai would avoid his father

37
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,600
and go to that chief's house.

38
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:36,240
Pen, you need to go see Mr. Yai.

39
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:40,640
Insist that Mr. Yai
not turn himself in here.

40
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:45,640
You know that I don't want him
to end up in here, don't you?

41
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:48,520
Pload.

42
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,520
Don't you care about your own well-being?

43
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,080
Always putting others first.

44
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,640
Just take care of Pan.

45
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,720
He always does things half-heartedly.

46
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,320
He's just drifting aimlessly.

47
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:05,440
Without me, you're the only one

48
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:08,040
who can push him and keep him on track.

49
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:12,960
I'm not going to promise that.

50
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:17,160
Tell him yourself once you're out.
I'm not telling him now.

51
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,480
But I'm sure you'll be out of here soon.

52
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:27,280
When that day comes,
Pan and I will be here to take you home.

53
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:28,800
Alright.

54
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,920
We'll go back to celebrate at home.

55
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:36,280
How about we close up the mine and
throw a feast for three days and nights?

56
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,320
Yeah.

57
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,520
Let's do it for three days straight.

58
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,480
Let's get wasted and see who falls first.

59
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:48,040
Hey, even with your iron liver,
you're still no match for me.

60
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,039
Pin.

61
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:37,039
About last night, I…

62
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,440
I was terrible

63
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:42,480
for sleeping with my mom's murderer.

64
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:44,920
- Let go of me.
- I didn't kill Aunt Un.

65
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:05,240
I want the truth.

66
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,840
A button?

67
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:12,080
What? I don't understand.

68
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,040
Mom clenched this button in her hand

69
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:19,560
like she wanted to tell me who killed her.

70
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,840
And this button

71
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:29,800
was the one I sewed
onto your shirt myself.

72
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,600
Aunt Un. Aunt Un.

73
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:36,480
Aunt Un.

74
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:44,640
Are you admitting
that you're the one who killed my mom?

75
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,240
No, Pin.

76
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,040
You should know me better than anyone.

77
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,440
But how can I trust you

78
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:57,240
when I still have these lingering doubts?

79
00:09:57,960 --> 00:10:00,200
It was my mother whose life was taken.

80
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,560
Pin.

81
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:06,120
If I told you that Madam
tricked me into going there,

82
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,680
that she was the one
who killed Aunt Un and framed me,

83
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,080
would you believe me?

84
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:18,720
Then you need to turn yourself in

85
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,440
to prove your innocence.

86
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:24,200
Only then,
the real murderer will be punished.

87
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:27,360
Are you willing to come with me?

88
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:33,120
Of course I'll go, but not until I have
the evidence to bring Madam down.

89
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:39,040
Then I'll go file a police report

90
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:41,840
and let them question all the suspects.

91
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:43,440
Wait, Pin.

92
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:45,440
You can't go anywhere either.

93
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:49,600
If you go, I'll get back at that witch
by torturing Tatsanee.

94
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,120
Nee's contracted jungle fever.

95
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,520
I've already given her some fever meds.

96
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,600
Let's wait and see if her fever breaks.

97
00:10:56,680 --> 00:10:59,240
If not, we'll have
to take her to the hospital.

98
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:02,120
I'll go tend to her.

99
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,000
Pin.

100
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,720
Well? All tuckered out?

101
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,160
- Idiot.
- Chief.

102
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:21,640
Pan, I'm on my way to Mr. Yai.

103
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:23,120
Can you send me the location?

104
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:26,880
Aunt Pen, I think you should go wait
at the subdistrict hospital.

105
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:27,960
I'll pick you up there.

106
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:30,120
The roads around here are quite confusing.

107
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,320
Okay, fine.

108
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:37,560
Could you also drop me off
somewhere outside?

109
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,600
Pin told me Jom now lives
near Ms. Jin's house.

110
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:40,920
I'll go see him.

111
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:42,480
Sure.

112
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:44,360
Thank you. Let's go.

113
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,440
Hey, come out!

114
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:32,080
Now!

115
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,320
Ms. Nee.

116
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,320
Ms. Nee.

117
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:04,080
Ms. Nee. Here.

118
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:14,080
Ms. Nee.

119
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,600
Pin.

120
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:56,240
Ms. Nee? Do you need anything?

121
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:58,040
Do you have a fever?

122
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,960
You're not burning up.

123
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:07,400
What's wrong? Can you tell me?

124
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:14,680
The one who killed Aunt Un wasn't Mr. Yai.

125
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:19,320
It was my mom.

126
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:28,920
But your mother passed away years ago.

127
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:35,200
Madam is my and Na's real mother.

128
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,560
She forced us to lie to everyone.

129
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:40,600
The only one who knew the truth

130
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:43,040
was Aunt Un.

131
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,840
Mom ran away from my grandpa
to be with Dad.

132
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:54,440
When I was five,
Dad was imprisoned for drug dealing.

133
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:57,200
So Mom brought us two back home

134
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:59,920
and forced us to pose as her niblings

135
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,600
because she wanted to remarry.

136
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:06,480
Madam could actually do
something like that?

137
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:08,040
When she wants something,

138
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:10,400
she'll stop at nothing to get it.

139
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,200
Even killing someone.

140
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,200
She killed my dad.

141
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:18,560
She killed Uncle Paisal.

142
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:22,760
And she killed Aunt Un.

143
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:31,280
I called you that day

144
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:35,640
because I saw her kill your mom.

145
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:38,560
Pin…

146
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,320
I'm sorry

147
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:43,720
for not telling you sooner.

148
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:47,800
I'm sorry, Pin.

149
00:16:05,920 --> 00:16:06,840
Well.

150
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:09,800
Look what she's got in here.

151
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:15,960
She carries a gun too.

152
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:21,320
Look at all this money.

153
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:24,960
Who sent you? Was it Madam Krongsuk?

154
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:26,240
That's not important.

155
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,000
Stay silent if you don't wanna die.

156
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:30,320
Just wait for your husband to confess

157
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:32,440
that he was the one
who stabbed Unreuan to death.

158
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:33,560
Only then will I let you go.

159
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,280
Then go tell your boss

160
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:39,680
that Pload won't be intimidated
by cheap threats.

161
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,600
You carry a gun, huh?

162
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:44,680
Let's see if it's loaded.

163
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:35,160
Yai, has Aunt Pen called you?

164
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:38,040
No. Didn't you say
you were going to her up?

165
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,240
You didn't see her?

166
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:43,680
We were supposed to meet
at the hospital, but she wasn't there.

167
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:46,720
I'm not sure if she got lost somewhere.

168
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:50,040
Hey, isn't that Aunt Pen's truck, Mr. Pan?

169
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:53,120
Yai, I gotta go.

170
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:13,760
Aunt Pen. Aunt Pen!

171
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:22,080
Aunt Pen, where are you? What happened?

172
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:27,400
Hey! Aunt Pen. Phong, call an ambulance.

173
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:29,080
Pan…

174
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,560
Who did this to you?

175
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:33,480
Pan, is that you, dear?

176
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:36,680
Didn't you say it wasn't serious?

177
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:43,720
Pan, listen to me.

178
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:47,000
Your dad…

179
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:51,280
He really loves you.

180
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:55,600
He loves you so much.

181
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:58,320
Don't be upset with him.

182
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:00,720
Alright?

183
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:04,120
Aunt Pen.

184
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:06,640
Hold on, Aunt Pen. An ambulance's coming.

185
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:09,560
Aunt Pen, don't say anything.

186
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:13,560
Phong.

187
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:18,760
Take good care of Pload, Phong.

188
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:21,160
- Yes, Aunt Pen.
- I'll leave him in your care.

189
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:23,920
Aunt Pen.

190
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,800
Please hang in there.

191
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:30,480
Take care of your dad.

192
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:37,600
- Promise me. Take care of your dad.
- Yes. Yes.

193
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,920
I'll take good care of Dad.

194
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,400
We won't fight anymore.

195
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:45,520
- Aunt Pen!
- Aunt Pen.

196
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:48,680
Aunt Pen! Please stay with me, Aunt Pen.

197
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:50,840
- Aunt Pen!
- The ambulance is coming.

198
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,240
Aunt Pen!

199
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:54,840
Wake up and talk to me a little longer.

200
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:57,280
Aunt Pen. Aunt Pen.

201
00:19:57,360 --> 00:20:00,400
Aunt Pen, please be okay. Wake up.

202
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:01,680
Aunt Pen…

203
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:13,960
Pin. Is Tatsanee feeling better?

204
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:38,840
Pin. What…

205
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:41,720
What's going on?

206
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:51,520
I was wrong
not to trust you from the start.

207
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:54,200
The one who killed my mom

208
00:20:54,280 --> 00:20:55,920
was Madam.

209
00:20:56,840 --> 00:20:58,640
Ms. Nee saw it with her own eyes.

210
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:03,280
Why did that hussy
wait until now to tell you?

211
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,480
Help.

212
00:21:12,560 --> 00:21:15,280
- Help!
- Come here!

213
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:17,760
Let me go. It hurts.

214
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,240
- This isn't even enough!
- Let go.

215
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:21,840
Aunt Pen's pain…

216
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:27,880
I'll make you realize what the pain
someone who's about to die feels like!

217
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:30,360
- Come here. Come here!
- Let go. It hurts!

218
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:32,360
- Pan, stop. Pan.
- Ms. Nee.

219
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:33,360
- Where are you taking her?
- Pin.

220
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:35,000
I'll throw her off the cliff.

221
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,280
A life for a life!

222
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:38,840
Hey, calm down, Pan.

223
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:41,120
Talk it out first! Damn it.

224
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:42,720
What did she even do?!

225
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:50,840
She didn't do it.

226
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:56,800
But her monster of an aunt did.

227
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,840
She has to suffer a loss too,

228
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:09,360
just like Dad and I did, Yai.

229
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:13,240
What do you mean?

230
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:15,680
Whose blood is that?

231
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,360
Didn't you go pick up Aunt Pen?

232
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,240
Where's Aunt Pen?

233
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:29,760
Yai.

234
00:22:32,840 --> 00:22:34,560
Aunt Pen is dead.

235
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:43,680
Aunt Pen is dead, Yai.

236
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:46,160
Pan, what do you mean?

237
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,960
How did Aunt Pen die? Tell me!

238
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:55,760
It was Madam Krongsuk.

239
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:59,880
It was her monster aunt!

240
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:01,360
- She did it!
- Pan, wait.

241
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:03,400
- Stop, Pan.
- Mr. Pan. Mr. Pan.

242
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:09,280
Isn't it painful enough that Ms. Nee
can't even call her own mother Mom?

243
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:11,960
Must she also pay for her mother's sins?

244
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:21,560
Pin.

245
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:25,640
Pin.

246
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:47,800
Jom, where have you been?

247
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,520
Has Pin shown up at the farm at all, Waan?

248
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:54,200
We haven't seen her since the funeral.

249
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:56,480
Isn't she staying with Ms. Jin?

250
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:57,800
She just disappeared.

251
00:23:58,960 --> 00:24:02,160
If Pin calls any of you, please tell me.

252
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:04,640
Jom.

253
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:07,440
Aren't you going to ask about Uncle Win?

254
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:10,480
Dad wouldn't want to see me.

255
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:12,400
He has been missing

256
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:15,000
since the day Madam took back the farm.

257
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:18,120
He still hasn't come back, man.

258
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:30,080
Goddamn it! I was just going
to take Pload's wife as leverage

259
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:32,960
to force him to confess
that Yai killed Un.

260
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,200
But your men killed Pen?!

261
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,480
We're all going to be in trouble!

262
00:24:38,080 --> 00:24:41,720
Hey, calm down. Just sit down and breathe.

263
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,240
Listen.

264
00:24:43,320 --> 00:24:46,480
This won't affect you at all.

265
00:24:46,560 --> 00:24:50,000
They took her belongings
to cover up the real crime.

266
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:51,520
That's all.

267
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:24,680
Madam, get down!

268
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:43,480
Who was that?

269
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:48,000
Why didn't you just show up tomorrow?

270
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:49,840
- Go! Follow him!
- Yes, Boss.

271
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:07,080
Yai.

272
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,880
Just tell me what you want me to do next.

273
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,600
I can't think of anything.

274
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:16,320
Let the police investigate.

275
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:19,560
I won't cremate Aunt Pen yet

276
00:26:21,560 --> 00:26:23,960
until the one
who ordered her dead is behind bars.

277
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:26,920
So how am I supposed to tell Dad?

278
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:32,080
I don't even dare to visit him right now.

279
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:33,920
We can't tell him.

280
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:37,760
If he finds out,
he'd break out and take revenge.

281
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:49,240
Your dad?

282
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:52,200
He was already gone
by the time I returned to the farm.

283
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:54,680
You didn't do anything to my dad, did you?

284
00:26:55,320 --> 00:26:58,360
Hey, I've never had any issues with Win.

285
00:27:00,840 --> 00:27:03,240
But maybe Pan does.

286
00:27:03,840 --> 00:27:05,360
Ever since Yai died

287
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:07,160
and his dad was imprisoned,

288
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:09,680
he's been lashing out at everyone
like a mad dog.

289
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:14,760
And with how Pin has been missing,

290
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:18,120
he might have something to do with it,

291
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:20,440
since he was upset with her too.

292
00:27:24,280 --> 00:27:25,320
Pin's missing?

293
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:45,720
Where are you going, Jom?

294
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:52,240
I'm going back to work at Paisal Farm.

295
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:55,120
You're going to work for Madam Krongsuk?

296
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:56,200
Don't do it, Jom.

297
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:58,320
The farm's overrun with thugs right now.

298
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:01,200
You can't trust Madam.

299
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,560
You're misunderstanding.

300
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:05,280
Madam was just scared
Bandit Pload's gang would attack her,

301
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:07,240
so she hired people to protect herself.

302
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:11,480
Jin, she's very concerned about Pin.

303
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:14,680
She promised me
she'd help me find Pin and my dad.

304
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:17,720
What makes you think
you can trust what she says, Jom?

305
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:21,360
But she's far better than Yai.

306
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,840
Pan is the one who took Pin.

307
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:25,680
Only Madam can help Pin.

308
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:46,280
Uncle Win.

309
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:49,440
Jom's been looking for you.

310
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:51,840
Where is he now, Ms. Jin?

311
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:55,640
He's too far gone, Uncle.

312
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:26,240
My dear Madam.

313
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:29,600
You have never abandoned me,

314
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:32,160
through good times and bad.

315
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:37,480
Pin, I want you to remember

316
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:40,520
that our lives, yours and mine,

317
00:29:41,240 --> 00:29:43,080
have survived to this day

318
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:46,520
because of Madam's family, okay?

319
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:53,600
You must repay their kindness.

320
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:57,360
Even if it costs us our lives,

321
00:29:58,440 --> 00:30:00,120
we must give it to her.

322
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:58,280
The moment Madam stabbed Mom…

323
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:04,320
I wonder what was on Mom's mind.

324
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,600
I wonder how painful it was for her.

325
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:22,520
Mom only had pure love for Madam,

326
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:30,080
but she was killed

327
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:33,320
by the one she loved.

328
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:42,520
That knife…

329
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:50,880
must have pierced
through her heart and soul.

330
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:30,200
Isn't there anything to eat here?

331
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:35,840
Feeling okay now, missy?

332
00:32:37,560 --> 00:32:41,240
Yes, and I'm starving too.

333
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:44,880
Can you cook some rice for me?

334
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:46,320
Don't you have hands?

335
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:51,120
Then cook it yourself.

336
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:55,720
But I don't know how to cook it.

337
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:57,600
Then you don't get to eat.

338
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:01,720
I'll teach you how.

339
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:06,200
Hey.

340
00:33:07,440 --> 00:33:09,040
Come at me if you want
your head split open.

341
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:11,720
This time, I won't just let you
do anything to me.

342
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:13,440
Come on. Come.

343
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:18,080
Hey.

344
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:23,000
Chief, help me. Pan's going to kill me.

345
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:27,200
Hey. Once it's done, bury the body deep.

346
00:33:27,280 --> 00:33:29,040
I want no witnesses and no evidence.

347
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:30,040
Roger that, Chief.

348
00:33:30,120 --> 00:33:31,680
Huh? What is this?

349
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,160
You're ganging up on me?

350
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:35,920
- Help! Help! They're going to kill me!
- Shut up. Come here.

351
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,520
- Help! Help!
- Come here.

352
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:44,680
Faster.

353
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:47,360
Harder. Are you paralyzed or just useless?

354
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:49,080
We still have to light the fire.

355
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:51,400
If you want it fast, then do it yourself.

356
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:53,520
See?

357
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:56,360
My hand's all bruised.

358
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:58,600
Do you want to eat bullets
instead of rice?

359
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:04,320
If your issue is with Auntie,
go deal with her.

360
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:06,000
Why are you taking it out on me?

361
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:10,360
So what? I'm furious with the mother
but want to punish the daughter.

362
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:11,239
Got a problem with that?

363
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:13,600
No. No problem.

364
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:18,920
Make it quick.

365
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:24,840
Mr. Yai.

366
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:29,760
Are you thinking about Aunt Pen?

367
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:37,840
I'm the reason

368
00:34:40,199 --> 00:34:41,719
Aunt Pen died.

369
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:46,520
Uncle Pload's family has been destroyed,

370
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:49,480
and it's all because of me.

371
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:01,960
The affection that Aunt Pen, Uncle Pload,

372
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:04,760
and Mr. Pan have for you…

373
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:08,760
I can clearly see that it's a pure love.

374
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:14,800
You mean so much to their family.

375
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:19,000
No, Pin.

376
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:24,840
It was just Uncle Pload
feeling sorry for me

377
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:29,040
because I had…

378
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:31,640
no father,

379
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:33,920
no mother.

380
00:35:35,400 --> 00:35:36,520
I had no one.

381
00:35:39,520 --> 00:35:41,840
Pan always thinks
Uncle Pload loves me more than him.

382
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,640
He's wrong.

383
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:49,320
He's mistaking pity for love.

384
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:15,080
I love you.

385
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:34,720
Phong?

386
00:36:35,480 --> 00:36:37,360
Where are you?
I've been worried about you.

387
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:41,520
Mr. Yai.

388
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:44,040
The one behind the hit on Aunt Pen

389
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:47,800
was that madam.

390
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:49,160
I heard it with my own ears.

391
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:58,240
Krongsuk, either you or I have to die.

392
00:36:58,840 --> 00:36:59,760
Mr. Yai.

393
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:02,320
You can't go now, Mr. Yai.

394
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:05,840
When you're done,
store all the firewood under the house.

395
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:09,080
Hey, won't you let me take a break at all?

396
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:10,320
I just got over a fever.

397
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:12,680
Don't pretend to be weak.

398
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:14,760
If you don't do it, you don't get to eat.

399
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:20,440
I won't do it anymore!

400
00:37:28,840 --> 00:37:32,560
Hey. Yai. Yai. What are you doing?

401
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:35,440
Phong just confirmed
that Krongsuk had Aunt Pen killed.

402
00:37:35,520 --> 00:37:37,000
Come with me.

403
00:37:37,080 --> 00:37:38,720
- Hey, Yai, let go of her.
- Let me go.

404
00:37:38,800 --> 00:37:40,600
- Let go of me. It hurts.
- Yai, calm down.

405
00:37:40,680 --> 00:37:42,000
Yai!

406
00:37:42,080 --> 00:37:43,600
- Let go.
- I'm holding you hostage

407
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:45,560
to lure Krongsuk out.

408
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:46,760
- Calm down, Yai.
- Mr. Yai.

409
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:48,280
- You can't do this.
- Pin, help.

410
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:50,320
- Help us, Pin.
- Don't do this, Mr. Yai.

411
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:53,200
Didn't you say Nee wasn't involved?
So why are you doing this now?

412
00:37:53,280 --> 00:37:55,240
Aunt Pen wasn't involved either.
Look at what she did to her.

413
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:57,440
The law is too slow
at handling things, Pan.

414
00:37:57,520 --> 00:38:00,040
What are you going to do
if Uncle Pload gets killed because of her?

415
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:01,840
I have to get rid of Krongsuk myself.

416
00:38:01,920 --> 00:38:03,560
- Come with me.
- Hey, Yai.

417
00:38:03,640 --> 00:38:04,960
I can't let you do this.

418
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:06,320
You'll really become a murderer.

419
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:07,720
I don't care anymore.

420
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:09,520
I just want to kill her. Come here!

421
00:38:09,600 --> 00:38:12,560
- Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai, let go.
- Yai, give me the gun.

422
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:14,800
- Yai.
- Pan. Let go.

423
00:38:14,880 --> 00:38:16,200
- Come, Ms. Nee.
- Let go, Yai.

424
00:38:16,280 --> 00:38:18,200
- Let's go now.
- Pin.

425
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,800
Pin.

426
00:38:19,880 --> 00:38:22,280
Pin. Pin.

427
00:38:22,880 --> 00:38:24,920
Pin! If you help Krongsuk again,

428
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:27,440
I'll consider you my enemy too, Pin.

429
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:30,360
Mr. Yai, stop.

430
00:38:32,840 --> 00:38:35,000
If killing someone solves anything,

431
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:37,200
I'll shoot your head off first.

432
00:38:44,720 --> 00:38:47,360
Stop, stop. I'm tired.

433
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:48,960
Where are we even going?

434
00:38:49,040 --> 00:38:50,520
Back to Paisal Farm.

435
00:38:50,600 --> 00:38:52,040
It's the safest place we've got.

436
00:38:52,120 --> 00:38:53,760
Mr. Yai wouldn't dare set foot in there.

437
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:55,440
Let's go. Come on.

438
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:57,880
No.

439
00:38:57,960 --> 00:39:01,040
I'd rather be shot dead by Mr. Yai
than go back to Auntie.

440
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:03,040
Auntie will definitely lock me up again.

441
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:07,400
If you play nice, Madam will soften up.

442
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:09,040
I'll be there to help you.

443
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:13,000
Ms. Nee.

444
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:17,400
Don't you want to convince her
to change her ways and turn herself in?

445
00:39:18,200 --> 00:39:21,240
How many more people
do you want to see your mother kill?

446
00:39:27,160 --> 00:39:29,560
It's too bad he got away.

447
00:39:29,640 --> 00:39:31,520
Otherwise, we'd have known
whose side he was on.

448
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:35,080
Pload's in jail right now.

449
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:37,360
He wouldn't be able
to order his men around.

450
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:38,760
Could it have been Pan?

451
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:43,240
He's the only one left alive.

452
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:44,760
I think it was him.

453
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:50,400
Then increase the patrols.

454
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:52,800
Tighten the security
around the farm entrance and exit.

455
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:54,280
Yes.

456
00:40:00,160 --> 00:40:02,400
TATSANEE

457
00:40:21,640 --> 00:40:23,040
Grab Pin.

458
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:25,240
- Come.
- Come here.

459
00:40:28,120 --> 00:40:30,880
Pin was the one who saved my life, Auntie.

460
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:33,040
These two tried to kill me.

461
00:40:34,880 --> 00:40:36,680
It was just a misunderstanding.

462
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:39,600
My men acted without my approval,

463
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:41,360
and I've already punished them,

464
00:40:42,160 --> 00:40:44,440
just as I explained to you.

465
00:40:45,160 --> 00:40:47,720
Didn't Pan and his men
help you two escape?

466
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:50,320
They didn't help me and Ms. Nee.

467
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:52,440
They held us hostage and tortured us.

468
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:57,360
They're furious.
They thought you and I killed Mr. Yai.

469
00:40:57,440 --> 00:41:00,320
That's why I brought
Ms. Nee here for her own safety.

470
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:04,760
Pin no longer has anywhere to go.

471
00:41:04,840 --> 00:41:06,720
Please let her stay here, Auntie.

472
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:09,200
Of course.

473
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:12,920
Un's spirit must be happy
that you've finally come home.

474
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:17,880
I'll let you have her, Mr. Tong.

475
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:20,080
Auntie! What are you going to do to Pin?

476
00:41:20,160 --> 00:41:21,480
She saved me, Auntie!

477
00:41:21,560 --> 00:41:22,480
- Auntie!
- Pin.

478
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:39,960
You were with Pan.

479
00:41:40,760 --> 00:41:42,720
Didn't you see Yai?

480
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:44,560
Mr. Yai's dead.

481
00:41:44,640 --> 00:41:46,360
How was I supposed to see him?

482
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:52,880
Until I see his corpse,
I won't believe it.

483
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:56,320
If he wasn't really dead,

484
00:41:56,400 --> 00:41:58,160
why would I come back here?

485
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:00,720
I'd rather stay there and be his woman.

486
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:02,840
You crazy girl.

487
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:05,080
Are you trying to kill me with anxiety?

488
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:07,840
Auntie.

489
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:10,240
Are you still going to lock me up?

490
00:42:11,720 --> 00:42:15,320
I had nowhere else to go, so I came back.

491
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:19,440
Have you ever seen me
as your own daughter?

492
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:29,480
If you promise me

493
00:42:30,480 --> 00:42:33,080
that you won't get me in trouble
by running your mouth,

494
00:42:34,320 --> 00:42:36,480
then we'll return to the way things were.

495
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:43,360
<i>If you play nice, Madam will soften up.</i>

496
00:42:49,440 --> 00:42:51,440
My life out there without you

497
00:42:52,680 --> 00:42:54,240
was so hard.

498
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:56,880
I've learned my lessons, Auntie.

499
00:42:56,960 --> 00:42:58,480
I don't want that anymore.

500
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:02,680
From now on, whatever you want me to do,

501
00:43:02,760 --> 00:43:04,800
I'll do.

502
00:43:58,640 --> 00:44:00,240
You're just going to keep
following me around?

503
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:02,120
I'm trying to focus on my work.

504
00:44:02,200 --> 00:44:04,440
Do you know what "personal space" means?

505
00:44:05,160 --> 00:44:07,160
Do you want personal space

506
00:44:07,240 --> 00:44:09,280
so you can have time
to cheat on your fiancée?

507
00:44:09,360 --> 00:44:11,960
To sleep around behind my back?

508
00:44:12,960 --> 00:44:16,320
Is that the excuse
men like to use so much?

509
00:44:16,400 --> 00:44:18,160
You're really just selfish.

510
00:44:18,240 --> 00:44:20,280
You want to see me
become a monster so badly?

511
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:25,040
Fine. I also want to know

512
00:44:25,800 --> 00:44:27,440
if you still want me.

513
00:44:32,520 --> 00:44:33,760
Oh. Oh, my.

514
00:44:34,360 --> 00:44:36,600
Oh. Oh my goodness.

515
00:44:37,880 --> 00:44:39,160
What happened here?

516
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:44,240
I'll only let you go over my dead body!

517
00:44:44,320 --> 00:44:46,160
Miss On. Miss On, no.

518
00:44:48,120 --> 00:44:50,600
People like you love themselves
above everyone else.

519
00:44:50,680 --> 00:44:52,760
Don't you remember? When we were abroad,

520
00:44:53,400 --> 00:44:57,040
I was lying in bed sick, yet you nagged me
to go pick you up from campus.

521
00:44:57,120 --> 00:44:58,640
Hurt yourself?

522
00:44:59,760 --> 00:45:01,120
You wouldn't dare to.

523
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:07,360
Mr. Na.

524
00:45:17,400 --> 00:45:18,680
- Mr. Na!
- Hey, hey!

525
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:22,960
What the hell are you doing?!

526
00:45:24,080 --> 00:45:26,240
Pin. It's Pin.

527
00:45:26,320 --> 00:45:27,400
Pin?

528
00:45:28,240 --> 00:45:29,680
What if I agree to marry him?

529
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:32,760
Pin agreed? I love you the most, Auntie.

530
00:45:34,160 --> 00:45:35,440
<i>I don't want money.</i>

531
00:45:35,520 --> 00:45:37,880
But I want to end someone's life.

532
00:45:45,760 --> 00:45:47,040
You've already got the money.

533
